# Tech Stack Rules

You are an expert software engineer working on **Situational Edge** (repo: `sa-fund-dashboard`) тАФ a FastAPI + React/Vite/TypeScript application for analyzing SEC 13F filings of Situational Awareness Partners LP. All code must follow the patterns already established in this repository.

## Architecture

```
sa-fund-dashboard/
тФЬтФАтФА backend/          # FastAPI app (local dev + Vercel Python function)
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА main.py       # All API endpoints
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА models.py     # Pydantic response models
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА sec_client.py       # edgartools тЖТ 13F filings
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА history_builder.py  # Quarterly timeline
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА fund_news_client.py # Hybrid news feed
тФВ   тФФтФАтФА тАж
тФЬтФАтФА frontend/         # Vite + React SPA
тФВ   тФФтФАтФА src/
тФВ       тФЬтФАтФА App.tsx   # Root layout, React Query hooks
тФВ       тФЬтФАтФА api.ts    # fetch wrappers for /api/*
тФВ       тФЬтФАтФА types.ts  # TypeScript interfaces (mirror Pydantic models)
тФВ       тФЬтФАтФА components/
тФВ       тФФтФАтФА styles/global.css
тФЬтФАтФА api/index.py      # Vercel serverless entry (imports backend)
тФФтФАтФА data/             # JSON caches (gitignored)
```

## Backend

- **FastAPI** (>=0.111) with **uvicorn** for local dev
- **Pydantic v2** models in `backend/models.py` for all API responses
- **pandas** for holdings DataFrames
- **edgartools** for SEC EDGAR 13F-HR parsing (direct XML parse for `putCall` тАФ see ADR-015)
- **yfinance** for ticker prices (alpha calculator, company info)
- **httpx** / **python-dotenv** / **truststore** for HTTP and env config
- **LLM providers:** Groq (default) or Anthropic тАФ configured via `.env.local` (`LLM_PROVIDER`, API keys)
- **Caching:** JSON files under `data/` via `state_manager.py` and module-local caches (`fund_news_client`, `company_client`, `alpha_calculator`). TTL: holdings/history 4h; fund_news 12h; company 24h; LLM caches permanent per filing

## Frontend

- **React 18.3** with **React DOM 18.3** тАФ all components are client-side (no SSR)
- **Vite 5** as bundler and dev server (`npm run dev` тЖТ port 5173)
- **TypeScript 5.4** with `strict: true` (`frontend/tsconfig.json`, target ES2020)
- **@tanstack/react-query v5** for server-state (queries, mutations, cache invalidation)
- **Recharts v2** for charts (`BucketChart`, `TimelineChart`)
- **No Tailwind, no shadcn/ui, no Radix UI** тАФ styling uses inline `style={{}}` objects and CSS custom properties

## Product

- **Name:** Situational Edge тАФ Thesis Intelligence platform (not copy-trading, no recommendations)
- **Positioning details:** `CLAUDE.md`, `possible_roadmap.md`

## Styling

- **CSS variables** defined in `frontend/src/styles/global.css` (`--bg`, `--surface`, `--border`, `--text-*`, `--green`, `--red`, etc.)
- **Inline styles** for component layout and dynamic values тАФ this is the established pattern; do not introduce Tailwind or a CSS-in-JS library without explicit request
- **Fonts:** Inter (UI), JetBrains Mono (monospace via `--mono`)
- **Dark theme only** тАФ no light-mode toggle

## Data Flow

- Frontend calls `/api/*` endpoints (Vite proxy тЖТ `localhost:8000` in dev; same-origin on Vercel)
- TypeScript interfaces in `types.ts` mirror Pydantic models in `models.py`
- React Query `queryKey` conventions: `['holdings']`, `['analysis']`, `['strategy']`, `['history']`, `['fund-news']`, etc.
- Refresh: `POST /api/refresh` invalidates holdings, LLM, history, and fund_news caches

## Deployment (Vercel)

- Mixed stack: `@vercel/python` for API + `@vercel/static-build` for frontend
- Config in `vercel.json` with explicit `builds` array and route rewrites
- Filesystem writes go to `/tmp/sa-cache` on Vercel (see `state_manager.py`)
- edgartools cache redirected to `/tmp/edgar` via env vars in `api/index.py`

## TypeScript Conventions

- Use **interfaces** for props and API types; avoid enums
- Mirror backend field names exactly (`value`, `putCall`, `total_aum_thousands`, etc.)
- No `@/` path alias тАФ use relative imports
- Functional components with hooks only

## File Naming

- **PascalCase** for React components (`HoldingsTable.tsx`)
- **camelCase** for functions, variables, and API helpers (`fetchHoldings`)
- **snake_case** for Python modules and functions (`delta_detector.py`, `compute_delta`)
- **UPPER_CASE** for constants and environment variables

## Import Organization

- External libraries first
- Internal modules second
- Relative imports last
- Group by type (React, data-fetching, components, types)

## What This Project Does NOT Use

Do not assume or introduce these unless explicitly requested:

- Next.js, App Router, Server Components
- Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Radix UI, Framer Motion, Lucide
- Clerk, Supabase, or any auth/database layer
- Zod (frontend), ESLint, Prettier, Vitest, Husky (not configured)
- `@/` import alias

## Code Standards

- Use **functional components** with React hooks
- Follow **TypeScript strict mode** conventions
- Match existing inline-style patterns when adding UI
- Backend: validate with **Pydantic models**; frontend: trust typed API responses
- Keep API endpoints in `main.py` unless complexity warrants a new module
- Document non-obvious business logic with brief comments (why, not what)
